{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "By employing various algorithms and computational techniques, researchers have found that automated systems can effectively identify relevant studies, extract pertinent data, and even assess the quality of the selected literature [3,13,14,15].",
    "Those systems have been shown to reduce the time and effort required for literature reviews, although they vary in their ability to handle different types of literature and research questions [16,17].",
    "Additionally, automated tools have been found to support the reproducibility of literature reviews by providing transparent and repeatable search and selection processes [18,19,20,21].",
    "The integration of text mining and machine learning techniques has further enhanced the capabilities of these systems, enabling more sophisticated analysis and synthesis of large volumes of literature [22,17].",
    "However, challenges remain in terms of their ability to interpret results and provide complex insights into complex research areas."
  ],
